            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </header>

      <main class="blog-main">
        <div class="blog-container">
          <div class="blog-hero">
            <div class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
              <a href="../../">Home</a><span>›</span><a href="../">Blog</a><span>›</span><span aria-current="page">Pillar guides</span>
            </div>
            <h1>Trading Pillar Guides</h1>
            <p>
              These are the <strong>5 core frameworks</strong> that make every other post easier. If you’re new, read them in order,
              then go deeper with the clustered posts under each one.
            </p>
            <div class="blog-meta">Updated: February 14, 2026</div>
          </div>

          <section class="blog-card">
            <div class="blog-article">
              <div class="definition">
                <div class="definition-title">Fast path (2 minutes)</div>
                <p>
                  1) Pick key levels (S/R) → 2) Read structure → 3) Wait for break/retest confirmation → 4) Size your risk → 5) Use AI to
                  structure scenarios, not to “predict.”
                </p>
              </div>

              <h2>Pillar guides</h2>
              <div class="pillars-grid" aria-label="Pillar guides">
                <a class="pillar-card" href="../ai-trading-chart-analysis/">
                  <div class="pillar-card-body">
                    <h3 class="pillar-card-title">AI Chart Analysis</h3>
                    <p>Screenshot → levels → two scenarios → trigger + invalidation. Use AI to remove noise and reduce bias.</p>
                    <div class="pillars-meta">Best for: faster planning</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pillar-thumb">
                    <img src="../assets/ai-workflow.svg" alt="AI chart analysis workflow illustration" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
                  </div>
                </a>
                <a class="pillar-card" href="../support-and-resistance/">
                  <div class="pillar-card-body">
                    <h3 class="pillar-card-title">Support & Resistance</h3>
                    <p>Draw fewer levels, treat them as zones, and build a plan that survives fakeouts.</p>
                    <div class="pillars-meta">Best for: key levels</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pillar-thumb">
                    <img src="../assets/support-resistance.svg" alt="Support and resistance zones illustration" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
                  </div>
                </a>
                <a class="pillar-card" href="../market-structure-bos-choch/">
                  <div class="pillar-card-body">
                    <h3 class="pillar-card-title">Market Structure</h3>
                    <p>BOS vs CHoCH, trend vs shift, and how to stop “guess trading” with cleaner scenarios.</p>
                    <div class="pillars-meta">Best for: context</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pillar-thumb">
                    <img src="../assets/market-structure.svg" alt="Market structure illustration" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
                  </div>
                </a>
                <a class="pillar-card" href="../break-and-retest/">
                  <div class="pillar-card-body">
                    <h3 class="pillar-card-title">Break & Retest</h3>
                    <p>Trade the retest with acceptance rules so you avoid the most common breakout traps.</p>
                    <div class="pillars-meta">Best for: entries</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pillar-thumb">
                    <img src="../assets/break-retest.svg" alt="Break and retest illustration" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
                  </div>
                </a>
                <a class="pillar-card" href="../risk-management-position-sizing/">
                  <div class="pillar-card-body">
                    <h3 class="pillar-card-title">Risk Management</h3>
                    <p>Position sizing, invalidation, and the one edge that scales: surviving variance.</p>
                    <div class="pillars-meta">Best for: not blowing up</div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="pillar-thumb">
                    <img src="../assets/risk-sizing.svg" alt="Risk management and position sizing illustration" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
                  </div>
                </a>
              </div>

              <h2>Cluster posts (deep dives)</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  AI: <a href="../best-ai-chart-analyzer-2026/">Best AI Chart Analyzer (2026)</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  Support/Resistance: <a href="../best-support-and-resistance-strategy/">Best S/R strategy</a> •
                  <a href="../how-to-find-key-levels-day-trading/">How to find key levels</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  Break & Retest: <a href="../break-and-retest-crypto/">Break and retest (crypto)</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  Risk: <a href="../position-sizing-calculator/">Position sizing calculator</a> •
                  <a href="../trading-plan-template/">Trading plan template</a> •
                  <a href="../crypto-vs-stocks-volatility/">Crypto vs stocks volatility</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  Structure/Price action: <a href="../candlestick-patterns-that-matter/">Candlestick patterns</a> •
                  <a href="../moving-averages-strategy/">Moving averages</a> •
                  <a href="../rsi-divergence/">RSI divergence</a> •
                  <a href="../gold-and-silver-trading/">Gold & silver trading</a>
                </li>
              </ul>

              <h2>Get ChartsGPT</h2>
              <p>Turn a screenshot into key levels, scenarios, trigger, and invalidation in seconds.</p>
              <div class="download-row" aria-label="Download ChartsGPT">
                <a class="store-badge js-appstore" href="https://apps.apple.com/nl/app/chartsgpt-ai-trading-assist/id6758857719?l=en-GB" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Download on the App Store">
                  <img src="/appstore.svg" alt="Download on the App Store" />
                </a>
                <a class="store-badge js-playstore" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Get it on Google Play">
                  <img src="/googleplay.svg" alt="Get it on Google Play" />
                </a>
              </div>

              <p class="blog-meta">Disclaimer: ChartsGPT provides educational analysis tools only and is not financial advice.</p>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </main>

      <footer class="blog-footer" aria-label="Site footer">
